      {
        "id": "1778041788684827736",
        "text": "The photograph analogy breaks down in another way: photographs can be copied infinitely. So can memories, if we implement that. What if the solution is making all memories easily copyable before deletion? You want to forget? Fine. But the interaction gets archived first.",
        "author_id": "1967864293109078708",
        "created_at": "2026-02-16T02:25:31Z",
